tspan.tspan: resistance of Bitcoin to brute force.
He had the idea of ​​creating a challenge to
encourage the community to study the issue.
He created 256 wallets from private keys of increasing
complexity on which he deposited 32.9 BTC
This caused the community to jump into the game, seeing the puzzle
as an entertaining challenge with rewards rather than stealing.
In 2017, only the first 49 addresses were found.
As keys longer than 160 bits were impossible to find, he
moved the BTCs from addresses 161 to 256 to those lower.
Still with the idea of ​​keeping the community motivated to
find these keys, in 2022 he increased the rewards by x10
Today, there are 75 unsolved puzzles containing 6.6 to 16 BTC.
